[{"id":"VR188444","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram and a graph. The diagram consists of a beam, two horizontal parallel conducting plates, and a wire. The setup of the plates, beam, and wire is as follows. The top horizontal plate has potential V sub T. The bottom horizontal plate has potential V sub B equals 0. The beam of electrons is shown moving horizontally to the right, into the space between the two parallel plates. The wire is horizontal and in the plane of the page, underneath the two plates. The wire has a current of I that is directed to the right. The graph contains 6 data points in the fourth quadrant of the coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled I and the vertical axis is labeled V sub T. The data points begin slightly below and to the right of the origin and trend linearly downward and to the right.\" height=\"167\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR188444.g10.png\" width=\"600\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A beam of electrons moves to the right with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase v\"><math alttext=\"lowercase v\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> between two conducting plates and parallel to a wire with current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> directed to the right, as shown above. The bottom plate is grounded <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub B equals 0\"><math alttext=\"V sub B equals 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>(</mo><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the top plate has potential <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub T\"><math alttext=\"V sub T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Several values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are used. For each value, the potential <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub T\"><math alttext=\"V sub T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the top plate is adjusted until the beam is undeflected while it is between the plates. A graph of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub T\"><math alttext=\"V sub T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is shown. The procedure is repeated, but <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub T\"><math alttext=\"V sub T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is fixed and the speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase v\"><math alttext=\"lowercase v\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the electrons is adjusted to keep the beam undeflected. Which of the following graphs correctly shows <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase v\"><math alttext=\"lowercase v\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> for the new procedure?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR188444_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of 6 data points in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled I, and the vertical axis is labeled lowercase v. The data points begin slightly to the right of the origin near the top of the vertical axis and trend in a concave up curve that moves downward and to the right, starting steep and then becoming less steep, getting close to horizontal at the right end.\" height=\"163\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR188444.g12.png\" width=\"210\" /></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of 6 data points in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled I, and the vertical axis is labeled lowercase v. The data points begin to the right of the origin and trend in a concave up curve that moves upward and to the right with increasing slope.\" height=\"163\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR188444.g14.png\" width=\"210\" /></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of 6 data points in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled I, and the vertical axis is labeled lowercase v. The data points begin to the right of the origin approximately three quarters of the way up the vertical axis and trend horizontally to the right.\" height=\"163\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR188444.g16.png\" width=\"210\" /></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of 6 data points in the first quadrant of the coordinate plane with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis 